    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_42180_1842_05_16_page01.jpg"/>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE"/><choice><orig>Edgeworths Town</orig><reg>Edgeworthstown</reg></choice>
                        <date when="1842-05-16">May 16<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. 1842</date></dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    You will do me a service<lb/>
                    and a favor by affixing<lb/>
                    my name to the petition<lb/>
                    to the <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#House-of-Lords_ENK">House of Lords</placeName> in favor<lb/>
                    of <persName ref="./Personography.xml#StanP1">Lord <choice><orig>Mahons</orig><reg>Mahon's</reg></choice></persName> Copyright<lb/>
                    Bill -<lb/>
                </p>
                <p>
                    I am obliged to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#StanP1">Lord<lb/>
                    Mahon</persName> for suggesting to you<lb/>
                    to write to me and thank<lb/>
                    you for doing so - thus giving<lb/>
                    me an opportunity of <choice><orig>express =<lb/>
                    = ing</orig><reg>expressing</reg></choice> my sense of the public<lb/>
                    advantage to the literary world<lb/>
                    of the measure &amp; giving me also<lb/>
                    the pleasure &amp; honor of having<lb/>
                    my name in such good &amp;<lb/>
                    high company as among<lb/>
                    those you mention to me<lb/>
                    who have already signed<lb/>
                    this petition<lb/>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    I am Dear Sir<lb/>
                    Yours sincerely<lb/>
                    <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName><lb/>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_42180_1842_05_16_page02.jpg"/>
                        Do you know <persName ref="./Personography.xml#CostL1">Miss Costello</persName><lb/>
                        We have been much amused<lb/>
                        by her <title ref="./Workography.xml#Pilgr1">Pilgrimage to <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Auvergne_FR">Auvergne</placeName></title><lb/>
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        I have a curiosity to know<lb/>
                        what sort of a rose it is which<lb/>
                        she calls the <hi rend="underline">Provins</hi> = rose<lb/>
                        and which she says was<lb/>
                        brought over by the Crusaders<lb/>
                        <del>&amp;</del> Is it like what we call in<lb/>
                        <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#ENK">England</placeName> the <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Provence_FR">Provence</placeName><lb/>
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Is it a pale pink or a<lb/>
                        deep crimson - Did she bring<lb/>
                        over any cuttings of it -<lb/>
                        If you have any opportunity<lb/>
                        of seeing her will you ask these<lb/>
                        questions - Also will you<lb/>
                        ask her where in <persName ref="./Personography.xml#Volta1"><choice><orig>Voltaires</orig><reg>Voltaire's</reg></choice></persName><lb/>
                        works we can find mention<lb/>
                        of <persName ref="./Personography.xml#Louis14"><choice><orig>Luois</orig><reg>Louis</reg></choice> the fourteenth's</persName> notice<lb/>
                        and favors towards the <choice><orig>in<lb/>
                        habitants</orig><reg>inhabitants</reg></choice> of a peculiar District<lb/>
                        in <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Auvergne_FR">Auvergne</placeName> - <del></del><lb/>
                        We have looked over <del><choice><orig>Voltaires</orig><reg>Voltaire's</reg></choice></del><lb/>
                        General Index to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#Volta1"><choice><orig>Voltaires</orig><reg>Voltaire's</reg></choice></persName><lb/>
                        <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_42180_1842_05_16_page03.jpg"/>
                        Works and through his<lb/>
                        <title ref="./Workography.xml#Ageof1"><choice><orig>Siecle de Louis Quatorze</orig><reg>Le Siecle de Louis XIV</reg></choice></title> in<lb/>
                        vain -<lb/>
                        May 16. 1842.<lb/>
                        <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName><lb/>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
